name: Bugbug Village
address: GH6V+FMG, Jl. Telaga Ngembeng, Sengkidu, Kec. Manggis, Kabupaten Karangasem, Bali 80811, Indonesia
review 1: That village will stay in my mind!! The people are so kind and it is like they live in the past!! You can walk around in the small tiny roads and see the inside of their houses!!! The have public baths and most of the villagers are rice farmers!!! The view of the terrace is outstanding!!
review 2: Wonderful to spend an hour wandering the lanes of a local village.  Our driver was a little perplexed that we wished to go here and not a traditional ancient village. This is however everyday life, everyone was friendly and there were no other tourists.
review 3: A village beside main road to denpasar near Candidasa. You can see an dense village with mostly only motorcycle could access the road inside its village. Situated at hilly location, it's a unique old village of traditional balinese culture.
review 4: Certainly quite an experience. Puts life into perspective when invited to visit a home of another culture.
review 5: Very interesting place, beautiful and the people were very kind and friendly. Our driver took us there and we just walked. Beautiful views of rice fields and little glimpses of daily life.
